# 2p_riot_cannon_sfx — host. Verifies that a non-hitscan self-fire
# (Riot Cannon, WFIRE_SPREAD) plays its SFX on the firer's window.
#
# Pre-fix bug (M6 Bug B): client_handle_fire_event used to gate ALL
# self-fire SFX behind `is_self && from_active_slot`. But the predict
# path (weapons_predict_local_fire) plays SFX only for WFIRE_HITSCAN.
# Result: silent fire on the firer's window for every non-hitscan
# weapon (Riot Cannon / Plasma SMG / Mass Driver / Auto-Cannon /
# Frag Grenades / Micro-Rockets / Burst SMG / Sidearm).
#
# Fix: split the gate into `_sparks` (gate on active-slot for all
# fire kinds — predict drew the sparks) and `_sfx` (additionally
# require WFIRE_HITSCAN — predict drew the SFX only for that case).
#
# Host side: the host is authoritative, so its own fire goes through
# weapons_spawn_projectiles which has always played the SFX. We just
# need a remote shot to land on the host's audio path, AND a remote
# Riot Cannon LMB to land on the client's FIRE_EVENT handler. This
# script focuses on the client window — host stays passive.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/2p_riot_cannon_sfx_host
network host 24112
name HostA

loadout - "Pulse Rifle" "Sidearm" Light Standard

spawn_at 2240 984
peer_spawn 1 2540 984

aim 2540 956

at 130 shot t130_pre_match

# Client LMB-fires Riot Cannon at t=200; host should see the fire
# event come in.
at 215 shot t215_client_riot_cannon_fired

at 280 end
